com.inqwell.any

Class SerializedProcess

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inqwell.any.AbstractComposite
      • com.inqwell.any.AbstractMap
        • com.inqwell.any.PropertyAccessMap
          • com.inqwell.any.AnyMap
            • com.inqwell.any.SimpleMap
              • com.inqwell.any.SerializedProcess
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Any, Composite, Map, Process, Serializable, Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LockerProxy

    public class SerializedProcess
extends SimpleMap
implements Process
    An implementation of the Process interface which acts as a replacement for the various process objects in a server when they are placed in a serialization stream.

    In general, server side Process implementations should not, indeed cannot, be serialized. However, a representation in a stream allows them to be manipulated

    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • getLockWaitObject

        public Any getLockWaitObject()
        Description copied from interface: Process
        Return the object this process is waiting to acquire the lock on or null if this process is not currently waiting for a lock. A lock may be implicit (taken out as required by the system) or explicit (taken out by the user). Explicit locks may be temporarily relinquished if the locking process chooses to wait on a locked object for notification from another process.
        Specified by:
        getLockWaitObject in interface Process
